condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 1, A, 3 | Description :The Borrower shall transfer a portion of the proceeds of the Loan toITERPA under a subsidiary agreement (...) regarding the implementation of Part 2. B of the Project | Due Date :17-Dec-2007

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 1, B, 1, a | Description :The Borrower shall maintain until the completion of the Projectthe unit within SEDOP responsible for the management of the Project | Due Date :17-Dec-2007
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 1, B, 1, b | Description :The Borrower shall create and maintain until the completion of theProject a Steering Committee | Due Date :17-Dec-2007
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 1, B, 1, c | Description :The Borrower shall establish and maintain until completion of theProject, a procurement unit within the PMU | Due Date :17-Jan-2008

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 1, B, 3 | Description :The Borrower shall not carry out any Subproject without the Bank'sprior approval of such PIPs, until the Bank has approved 14 PIPs | Due Date :31-Dec-2008

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 1, B, 4 | Description :Prior to initiating any activity which will benefit or affect anindigenous community, the Borrower shall obtain from FUNAI (a) an agreement to carry out such activity, and (b) a commitment tocollaborate with the Borrower in carrying out such activity | Due Date :30-Jun-2008

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 1, B, 5 | Description :The Borrower shall (a) have the procurement procedures audited, (b)furnish to the Bank the report of such procurement audit, and (c) furnish to the Bank any other information concerning saidprocurement audit that the Bank may reasonably request | Due Date :30-Jun-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 1, C | Description :The Borrower shall ensure that the Project, including all Subprojects,is carried out in accordance with the provisions of the Anti-Corruption Guidelines | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 2, A, 1 | Description :The Borrower shall monitor and evaluate the progress of the Projectand prepare Project reports (...) on the basis of the indicators agreed with the Bank. each report shall cover the period of onecalendar semester. | Frequency :SemiAnnual

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 2, A, 2 | Description :The report on the execution of the Project and related plan shall befurnished to the Bank no later than 6 months before the Closing Date | Due Date :30-Jun-2014

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 2, B, 1 | Description :The Borrower shall maintain a FM system in accordance with theprovisions of Section 5.09 of the General Conditions. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 2, B, 2 | Description :The Borrower shall prepare and furnish to the Bank no later than 45days after the end of each calendar quarter, interim unaudited financial reports for the Project covering the quarter, in form andsubstance satisfactory to the Bank | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section 2, B, 3 | Description :The Borrower, through the PMU, shall have its Financial Statementsaudited (...). The audited Financial Statements for each such period shall be furnished to the Bank no later than 6 months afterthe end of such period | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A, 2 (a) | Description :The Borrower shall (i) transfer a portion of the proceeds of theLoan to BANPARA under a subsidiary agreement, and (ii) cause BANPARA to enter into an agreement with the relevant ProducerAssociations | Due Date :17-Dec-2007
